cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.CL 

The paper deals with automatic species classification in camera traps using deep learning techniques, which falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of regularization strategies and ensemble learning also suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of label smoothing, which is a common technique in natural language processing (cs.CL) but can also be applied to image classification tasks.
